    "summary": "Experienced Fund Manager with a demonstrated history of working in the impact investing and banking industry. Skilled in Public Programme Management, Impact Investing, Climate Finance and Development Finance. Seasoned professional in Blended Finance, Emerging Markets, Portfolio Management, Financial (Re-)Structuring, Banking, and Corporate Finance, with a MSc in Econometrics.\n\nMobilising Finance for Forests (MFF) is a Forest and Sustainable Land Use impact fund that FMO manages on behalf of the UK's Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy. MFF primary goal is to combat deforestation and environmental unsustainable land use practices. Increasing the value of standing forest and incorporating forest protection and reforestation in sustainable agricultural practices will aid climate action globally. The fund will invest through indirect and direct investment and has current funding of GBP 150 mln.\nhttps://www.fmo.nl/mff\n\nBuilding Prospects is an impact fund that FMO manages on behalf of the Dutch Ministry of Foreign Affairs. Building Prospects' primary goal is private sector development. The majority of the poor are dependent on and active in agribusiness. A sustainable agribusiness value chain needs access to infrastructure. And any business needs to take into account climate risk and invest in resilience to climate change. Building Prospects therefore invests in Agribusiness, Infrastructure and Climate. The Fund follows an inclusive approach, financing projects and companies that service individuals at the base of the pyramid taking care to actively include women and create an impact on Gender Equality. The Fund offers debt and equity solutions to its clients and currently has committed portfolio of over EUR 410mln in 60 investments. \n\nYou are invited to read more on our website: \nhttps://www.fmo.nl/building-prospects",
